There are mounting concerns over the increase of cholera cases. The NICD has already recorded six instances of infection with one death reported in Gauteng. To discuss this, we speak to Dr. Alinafe Kasiya, Country Director of the VillageReach in Malawi. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - There are mounting concerns over the increase in cholera cases. The NICD has already recorded six instances of infection, with one death reported in Gauteng. READ: African cholera cases falling but floods up risk: WHO The Department of Health says the most common way cholera spreads is through contaminated or polluted water. People can become infected directly by drinking unpurified water or indirectly through contaminated food. Watch the video above for more details.